
### 3. Add the README to Your Repository

1. Navigate to your repository on GitHub.
2. Click on "Add file" and select "Create new file".
3. Name the file `README.md`.
4. Copy and paste the content from the template above into the file.
5. Commit the new file.

### 4. Push Your Code to GitHub

1. Open your terminal or command prompt.
2. Navigate to your project directory.
3. Initialize a new git repository (if not already done):
   ```bash
   git init
